      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, quick question for my dissertation. if i'm looking at a p-value of 0.06 in my results, how do i explain why it's technically \"not significant\" even if the effect size looks pretty large and there's a clear trend in the graph? i'm struggling to frame the distinction between a \"trend\" and statistical significance for my defense.",
