      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The p-value of 0.06 simply means your evidence didn't quite meet the traditional threshold of $\\alpha = 0.05$ to confidently rule out pure chance. Think of your large effect size as a *plausible* finding, but the p-value tells you we haven't achieved sufficient statistical certainty for it. Framed for your defense, you can argue it shows a \"marginal tendency\" or \"risks-to-miss,\" acknowledging a strong prospective signal without declaring outright proof.",
